I got a couple scratches.

29:54.241 --> 29:58.042
I took a bit of a tumble getting
some of the bushes up there.

29:58.044 --> 29:59.610
A tumble? What kind of tumble?

29:59.612 --> 30:01.912
You okay?
Well, you know, it wasn't -

30:01.914 --> 30:03.413
wasn't really a tumble.

30:03.415 --> 30:04.847
It was kind of... - geez, John.

30:04.849 --> 30:06.682
You know we're nearly always
around over here

30:06.684 --> 30:09.184
if you need anything.

30:09.186 --> 30:10.618
You can pretend
you don't want these

30:10.620 --> 30:12.086
and make a fuss if you like,

30:12.088 --> 30:14.421
but I'm gonna make you, anyways.

31:34.669 --> 31:36.568
Hey, Danny.

31:39.139 --> 31:42.173
All right.

31:42.175 --> 31:44.341
Hey, uh...

31:44.343 --> 31:47.176
I'm sorry to hear
about your brother.

31:48.946 --> 31:51.546
You... you heard any news?

31:57.553 --> 32:01.354
Well, all right, bud.

32:01.356 --> 32:05.524
Uh, listen, I'll, uh...

32:05.526 --> 32:08.193
I'll... I'll just let you be.

32:08.195 --> 32:12.997
Sheriff seems to think
he got drunk and just fell in.

32:12.999 --> 32:16.833
They've been dragging that
God damn lake all afternoon.

32:16.835 --> 32:19.969
No body yet.

32:19.971 --> 32:21.870
Yeah.

32:21.872 --> 32:24.339
I heard.

32:24.341 --> 32:25.973
I doubt that, though.

32:28.177 --> 32:31.978
No way Dutch drowns in there.

32:31.980 --> 32:36.882
Well, let's hope not.

32:36.884 --> 32:40.485
They're just, you know,
doing what they can.

32:50.897 --> 32:53.898
You know, maybe, uh...

32:53.900 --> 32:57.601
maybe he just took off
for a bit, you know.

32:57.603 --> 33:00.337
Dodging somebody or something?

33:02.174 --> 33:03.740
Yeah.

33:03.742 --> 33:05.942
Plenty of reason for that,
lately.

33:09.514 --> 33:13.749
I've never seen a guy
so upset in my entire life.

33:13.751 --> 33:20.121
That vision or whatever
just scared the shit out of him.

33:20.123 --> 33:22.756
Yeah, I know.
I heard about that.

33:22.758 --> 33:24.624
You know, he had quite a bit
to say to a few people

33:24.626 --> 33:27.927
in particular.

33:27.929 --> 33:31.897
Did he come see
you the other evening?

33:31.899 --> 33:36.134
I haven't talked to Dutch in...
in a long time.

33:39.772 --> 33:42.105
To be honest, you know,
there's a lot of people in town

33:42.107 --> 33:46.609
have been pretty worried about
him for the last few weeks.

33:53.484 --> 33:55.984
Well...

33:55.986 --> 34:00.388
Like I said, I'll, uh...

34:00.390 --> 34:02.156
I'll just let you be.
You know, I'm sitting here

34:02.158 --> 34:05.125
because this is
where they found his truck.

34:05.127 --> 34:09.962
So, I figure,
this is where he bought it.

34:09.964 --> 34:12.097
And they say from time to time
that the killer

34:12.099 --> 34:16.967
will come on back to the scene
of the crime, you know.

34:16.969 --> 34:19.704
Oh... Yeah.

34:23.176 --> 34:24.775
So, the past few evenings,

34:24.777 --> 34:26.777
I've just been sitting here
having a few smokes

34:26.779 --> 34:29.612
and seeing who drives by.

34:29.614 --> 34:33.350
Well, pretty...

34:33.351 --> 34:35.284
pretty busy road, Danny,
you know?

34:35.286 --> 34:39.522
You must have seen a lot
of people passing by.

34:39.524 --> 34:42.157
Oh, yeah, quite a few.

34:48.498 --> 34:50.364
Oh, boy. More changes?

34:50.366 --> 34:51.764
Yes, correct, correct.

34:51.766 --> 34:54.434
- Are you filling him in?
- Yeah.

34:54.436 --> 34:57.503
All right, look. I'm... I'm leaving
...leaving to my car right now.

34:57.505 --> 34:59.805
Where am I meeting you?

34:59.807 --> 35:02.641
No, no, no, no. Just text me.

35:02.643 --> 35:04.509
No, just... just text me.

35:04.511 --> 35:08.011
I'm not writing it down.
Hey, listen.

35:08.013 --> 35:12.181
I got a dinner.

35:12.183 --> 35:14.483
I'll be home later.

35:14.485 --> 35:16.184
You post that.

35:16.186 --> 35:19.387
Call you when I get home.
Yeah, sure.

35:23.992 --> 35:26.591
Well, that guy is, um...

35:28.795 --> 35:30.294
What are the changes?

35:30.296 --> 35:33.363
Uh... Headband.

35:33.365 --> 35:35.331
Huh?

35:35.333 --> 35:38.735
The yogurt cup
is getting a headband.

35:38.737 --> 35:41.670
- Cool.
- Totally cool.

35:42.806 --> 35:46.073
[ Sighs ]

35:46.075 --> 35:48.742
All right,
I'll get us some dinner.

35:59.688 --> 36:01.454
Wow.

36:01.456 --> 36:03.022
- Hey.
- This looks great, thank you.

36:03.024 --> 36:04.156
Yeah, of course.

36:04.158 --> 36:06.625
I hope beer's okay.

36:06.627 --> 36:08.960
Yes, of course.

36:08.962 --> 36:10.261
Well?

36:10.263 --> 36:12.062
- Yeah.
- Okay.

36:26.444 --> 36:28.010
These are cute.

36:28.012 --> 36:29.878
I know, right?

36:32.949 --> 36:37.817
[ Chuckles ]

36:37.819 --> 36:40.119
How about this?

36:40.121 --> 36:44.790
Did you know kumquats are served
during Chinese spring festival?

36:47.060 --> 36:48.526
Uhhuh.

36:48.528 --> 36:52.997
Um, did you know that in winter,

36:52.999 --> 36:55.299
most parts of China
are quite cold?

36:55.301 --> 36:56.633
It doesn't say that.

36:56.635 --> 36:58.901
It does.

36:58.903 --> 37:00.502
That's a true fact.

37:00.504 --> 37:02.036
Wow, well...

37:02.038 --> 37:03.303
Now you know.

37:03.305 --> 37:04.971
Now you know.

37:04.973 --> 37:07.840
Uh... Looks like there's just one
of those.

37:07.842 --> 37:09.074
Do you want it?

37:09.076 --> 37:11.543
Oh, no, I can't do raw shrimp.

37:11.545 --> 37:14.546
It's okay. It's not.

37:14.548 --> 37:15.980
It's not?

37:15.982 --> 37:17.715
If it was raw, it'd be blue.

37:19.685 --> 37:23.086
Oh, God, you're right.
[ Chuckling ] I'm and idiot.

37:23.088 --> 37:24.987
Uh... Well, do you want it?

37:24.989 --> 37:27.155
- No, you have it.
- You ever had it?

37:27.157 --> 37:28.890
Yeah.

37:28.892 --> 37:31.726
It seems like you're lying.

37:31.728 --> 37:35.262
- I always thought it was raw.
- Well, you should have it.

37:35.264 --> 37:37.197
- No.
- Have it.

37:37.199 --> 37:39.365
- No.
- It's great.

37:39.367 --> 37:41.433
Okay.

37:41.435 --> 37:42.567
Graceful.

37:42.569 --> 37:45.570
Yeah, I'm just gonna do that.

37:51.677 --> 37:54.044
What do you think?

37:54.046 --> 37:55.678
Mm.

37:55.680 --> 37:57.446
Oh.

38:01.184 --> 38:03.751
Mm.

38:23.605 --> 38:26.138
Kate.

38:26.140 --> 38:26.640
Kate.

38:30.544 --> 38:32.076
Shit.

38:32.078 --> 38:33.710
Uh, it's posted.

38:33.712 --> 38:35.545
It's in right now.

38:37.081 --> 38:39.081
[ Keyboard clicks ]

38:39.083 --> 38:41.316
All right,
let's get out of here.

38:41.318 --> 38:42.983
Yeah, let's.

38:45.320 --> 38:46.886
This is me.

38:49.090 --> 38:51.523
Well, that sucked,
but you were great. Thanks.

38:53.560 --> 38:57.295
Yeah, the failing is mutual.

38:57.297 --> 38:59.330
The feeling... the feeling
and the failing,

38:59.332 --> 39:01.632
they're both mutual.

39:01.634 --> 39:04.234
Um... Do you think
this would fit?

39:04.236 --> 39:05.768
Oh, no. Don't worry about it.

39:05.770 --> 39:08.003
I got to keep my girlish figure,

39:08.005 --> 39:11.806
but, uh, you just get
a good night's...

39:11.808 --> 39:13.574
uh... You know.

39:13.576 --> 39:14.808
Good night.

39:14.810 --> 39:16.743
You, too. Get home safe.

39:16.745 --> 39:18.911
All right, I will. Thanks.

39:34.027 --> 39:36.660
[ Yawns ]

39:38.997 --> 39:41.830
[ Garage door opening ]

39:43.600 --> 39:46.200
[ Birds chirping ]

39:48.704 --> 39:51.337
[ Saw buzzing ]

41:01.408 --> 41:03.741
So, they...
they bring the guy in,

41:03.743 --> 41:05.509
and they don't know anything
about him.

41:05.511 --> 41:06.910
And they should ask
for his I.D.,

41:06.912 --> 41:08.544
and they look
through everything.

41:08.546 --> 41:10.212
And then finally they look
through his motorcycle.

41:10.214 --> 41:12.581
Guy looked like some kind
of a criminal.

41:12.583 --> 41:14.249
I don't know...
just, you know, you just

41:14.251 --> 41:16.517
can tell when you look
at some of these guys like that.

41:16.519 --> 41:18.085
Just... Morning there, fellas.

41:18.087 --> 41:19.586
- Hey.
- Hey, there, John.

41:19.588 --> 41:21.287
We're just talking
about the latest.

41:21.289 --> 41:23.922
- What's that?
- A guy they picked up yesterday

41:23.924 --> 41:26.724
over at the campground
in sauk, the biker guy?

41:26.726 --> 41:29.893
They're pretty sure he's got
everything to do with Dutch missing.

41:29.895 --> 41:31.427
What... what's that now?

41:31.429 --> 41:33.028
- Geez, John.
- What?

41:33.030 --> 41:35.096
You look like hell.

41:35.098 --> 41:36.363
I do?

41:36.365 --> 41:38.698
Yesterday afternoon,

41:38.700 --> 41:41.767
they had some kind
of a scuffle over there.

41:41.769 --> 41:44.302
And once the cops got him in,
turns out that he's got some

41:44.304 --> 41:46.470
heavy history with Dutch
over a bunch of money, I think.

41:46.472 --> 41:49.306
- Well, who he is?
- Some biker type from up north.

41:49.308 --> 41:50.940
Not a real gentle soul,
from what I gather.

41:50.942 --> 41:53.275
You know,
tattooed up all over the place,

41:53.277 --> 41:55.277
- one on the neck.
- Ooh!

41:55.279 --> 41:57.912
Apparently, he had something
like five grand in cash

41:57.914 --> 41:59.747
locked up in his chopper.
Five grand?

41:59.749 --> 42:01.315
Damn.
That's what I hear, anyway.

42:01.317 --> 42:02.983
Well, what are they saying
about he and Dutch?

42:02.985 --> 42:06.953
- Well, I mean, it's...
- He is a person of interest.

42:06.955 --> 42:08.287
Coffee?

42:08.289 --> 42:10.789
Yeah, coffee, yeah, thanks,
franny.

42:10.791 --> 42:12.824
Anyway, he's a suspect.

42:12.826 --> 42:15.760
Sounds like a no-brainer,
though, I mean.

42:15.762 --> 42:19.663
You know, speaking of...
speaking of harsh souls,

42:19.665 --> 42:22.298
I'll never understand why
that woman dislikes me so much.

42:22.300 --> 42:24.466
Maybe you should try tipping
her something one of these days.

42:24.468 --> 42:27.101
- I tip.
- More than nickels, I'm saying.

42:27.103 --> 42:29.770
Every day...
I'm here every God damn day,

42:29.772 --> 42:32.238
probably since she
was wetting her pants.

42:34.308 --> 42:36.308
Okay, look,
everything we've got so far

42:36.310 --> 42:38.510
is boring crap, okay?

42:38.512 --> 42:41.579
Now, I don't mind that every now and
then we're gonna put out some crap.

42:41.581 --> 42:44.481
Everybody does, but let's make
it interesting at least.

42:44.483 --> 42:46.649
I'd rather be interesting
and boring.

42:46.651 --> 42:49.918
If it's crap, let's make
it interesting crap, okay?

42:49.920 --> 42:52.186
We're gonna
role play like we're a bunch

42:52.188 --> 42:53.620
of fucking idiots, all right?

42:53.622 --> 42:55.488
For whatever reason,
we've got some kind

42:55.490 --> 42:57.323
of impaired cognitive function.

42:57.325 --> 43:01.026
Now, what would appeal to us?

43:01.028 --> 43:02.460
What do you got?

43:02.462 --> 43:04.495
Somebody hit a single.

43:37.963 --> 43:40.563
[ Sanding ]

43:45.335 --> 43:47.201
[ Blows ]

43:47.203 --> 43:49.803
[ Vehicle approaching ]

43:53.908 --> 43:56.808
[ Car door opens, closes ]

43:58.545 --> 44:00.478
John?

44:00.480 --> 44:04.815
Verne, how are you?

44:04.817 --> 44:06.183
Can't complain.

44:06.185 --> 44:07.684
You got a minute?

44:07.686 --> 44:09.218
Sure, of course.

44:09.220 --> 44:11.252
Can I get you a beer
or something, or...?

44:13.723 --> 44:15.622
Yeah, close enough, sure.

44:17.859 --> 44:20.426
How's Laura?
She just retired, yeah?

44:20.428 --> 44:22.528
Yeah... bored.

44:22.530 --> 44:24.062
Yeah.

44:24.064 --> 44:26.431
What you got there?

44:26.433 --> 44:29.267
Oh, those
are for the maitlands.

44:29.269 --> 44:32.069
They're doing some remodeling
and stuff over there.

44:32.071 --> 44:33.670
Jake maitland?

44:33.672 --> 44:35.405
Yeah, Jake.

44:35.407 --> 44:38.775
Hmm, funny.

44:38.777 --> 44:41.444
What's that?

44:41.446 --> 44:43.913
I'll just cut to the chase
here.

44:43.915 --> 44:47.717
Are you up to speed on
all this Dutch Miller business?

44:47.719 --> 44:50.486
Oh, yeah. I believe so.

44:50.488 --> 44:52.054
- Strange one, huh?
- That it is.

44:52.056 --> 44:54.222
You know, we're
dragging the lake over there.

44:54.224 --> 44:56.857
Yeah, over by that dam
and stuff, right?

44:56.859 --> 45:00.694
Nothing yet there,
but a couple days back,

45:00.696 --> 45:04.364
we get a call over to smoky's
campground over in sauk.

45:04.366 --> 45:07.800
Pick up this rough-looking
fellow from somewhere up north.

45:07.802 --> 45:11.303
Turns out, he and Dutch had
some big problems in the past.

45:11.305 --> 45:12.737
- Oh, yeah?
- Yeah.

45:12.739 --> 45:14.872
Thought we had something there.

45:14.874 --> 45:16.639
Turns out it was a dead end.

45:18.909 --> 45:20.541
For Dutch, anyway.

45:20.543 --> 45:24.177
Guy's got a bunch of cash
on him, so he's up to something,

45:24.179 --> 45:27.513
but God only knows.

45:27.515 --> 45:30.015
Anyways, in the midst
of all that,

45:30.017 --> 45:32.050
as soon as we let him go,

45:32.052 --> 45:33.718
Danny Miller got to drinking.

45:33.720 --> 45:36.887
He pays a visit
over to the campground himself.

45:36.889 --> 45:38.221
- Oh, yeah?
- Yeah.

45:38.223 --> 45:39.822
They got into it pretty good.

45:39.824 --> 45:42.558
Danny tagged him one on the jaw,
put him in the hospital.

45:42.560 --> 45:45.060
- Aw, geez Louise.
- Yeah.

45:45.062 --> 45:48.896
We're holding Danny there
right now, but not for long.

45:48.898 --> 45:51.498
Oh, no?

45:51.500 --> 45:54.767
Can't get a word
out of either one of them.

45:54.769 --> 45:57.903
If this is their regard
for their worst enemy,

45:57.905 --> 45:59.237
here's the police.

45:59.239 --> 46:00.938
Oh, geez, I see.

46:00.940 --> 46:02.739
Yeah.

